TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

The next two problems are like the preceding two.  So keep track of
your calculation in this problem so that you don't need to redo them
in the next problem. 

The solution of the linear system
\[
\begin{array}{rrrcr}
x &+2y &-5z &=& -32 \\
2x &-2y &+z&=& 15 \\
4x &-2y &+3z&=& 27 \\
\end{array}
\]

The solution of this system is 
$BR
\(x=\) \{ ans_rule(6) \},
EOT
&ANS(num_cmp("1"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
\(y=\) \{ ans_rule(6) \}, and
EOT
&ANS(num_cmp("-4"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
\(z=\) \{ ans_rule(6) \}.
EOT
&ANS(num_cmp("5"));

TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR Hint: 
Proceed carefully and systematically and use row sums to check your progress.
EOT

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD
We obtain
\[
\begin{array}{lrrrrr}
\hbox{equation} & x & y & z & RHS & RS \\
{[1]} & 1 & 2 & -5 & -32 & -34 \\
{[2]} & 2 & -2 & 1 & 15 & 16 \\
{[3]} & 4 & -2 & 3 & 27 & 32 \\
{[4]=[2]-2[1]}  & 0 & -6 & 11 & 79 & 84 \\
{[5]=[3]-4[1]} & 0 & -10 & 23 & 155 & 168 \\
{[6]=6[5]-10[4]} & 0 & 0 & 28 & 140 & 168 \\
\end{array}
\]


The last equation is \(28z=140\) which gives \(\underline{z=5}\).
Substituting \(z\) in equation \([4]\) gives
\(-6y+55=79\) or \(\underline{y=-4}\). Substituting \(y\) and \(z\) in
equation \([1]\) gives \(x-8-25 = -32\) or \(\underline{x=1}\).

EOT








